    {
      "id": "https://rob.crabapples.net/2026/07/21/day-four-gallup-to-fresno.html",
      "url": "https://rob.crabapples.net/2026/07/21/day-four-gallup-to-fresno.html",
      "title": "Day Four: Gallup to Fresno",
      "content_html": "<p>Day Four.</p>\n<p>We left Gallup, New Mexico at 6:30AM local time outbound to Fresno, California. We arrived in Fresno at 6:30PM local time. It works out to 13 hours becuase we had a shift in time from the Central time zone (CST) to Pacific (PST).</p>\n<p>We covered 783 miles or 1260 kilometers. I’m happy to be out of the car.</p>\n<p>I’ve had trouble sleeping on this trip for some reason. Last night I slept like a baby. I woke up at 5:30AM on my own, no alarm needed, which was nice.</p>\n<p>While we’re here I’m trying to stay as close to Eastern time as possible so I can work with my co-workers on their time.</p>\n<p>The nice thing about that is I’m off earlier because of the three hour time difference.</p>",
      "date_published": "2026-07-21T14:39:30+00:00",
      "authors": [
